#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Simple starting layout for a PyQt6 application.
Save as /home/josie/Documents/programming/python/pestprofessor/main.py
"""

from PyQt6.QtWidgets import (
    QApplication, QMainWindow, QPlainTextEdit, QFileDialog,
    QMessageBox, QToolBar, QStatusBar, QAction, QWidget, QVBoxLayout
)
from PyQt6.QtCore import Qt
import sys
from pathlib import Path


class MainWindow(QMainWindow):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.current_file: Path | None = None
        self.setWindowTitle("PestProfessor")
        self.resize(900, 600)
        self._create_actions()
        self._create_menus_and_toolbar()
        self._create_central_widget()
        self._create_status_bar()

    def _create_actions(self) -> None:
        self.open_act = QAction("Open...", self, shortcut="Ctrl+O", triggered=self.open_file)
        self.save_act = QAction("Save", self, shortcut="Ctrl+S", triggered=self.save_file)
        self.save_as_act = QAction("Save As...", self, shortcut="Ctrl+Shift+S", triggered=self.save_file_as)
        self.exit_act = QAction("Exit", self, shortcut="Ctrl+Q", triggered=self.close)
        self.about_act = QAction("About", self, triggered=self.about)

    def _create_menus_and_toolbar(self) -> None:
        file_menu = self.menuBar().addMenu("&File")
        file_menu.addAction(self.open_act)
        file_menu.addAction(self.save_act)
        file_menu.addAction(self.save_as_act)
        file_menu.addSeparator()
        file_menu.addAction(self.exit_act)

        help_menu = self.menuBar().addMenu("&Help")
        help_menu.addAction(self.about_act)

        toolbar = QToolBar("Main")
        toolbar.setMovable(False)
        toolbar.addAction(self.open_act)
        toolbar.addAction(self.save_act)
        self.addToolBar(toolbar)

    def _create_central_widget(self) -> None:
        container = QWidget()
        layout = QVBoxLayout()
        self.editor = QPlainTextEdit()
        self.editor.setPlaceholderText("Start typing...")
        layout.addWidget(self.editor)
        container.setLayout(layout)
        self.setCentralWidget(container)

    def _create_status_bar(self) -> None:
        self.status = QStatusBar()
        self.setStatusBar(self.status)
        self.status.showMessage("Ready")

    def open_file(self) -> None:
        path, _ = QFileDialog.getOpenFileName(self, "Open File", "", "Text Files (*.txt);;All Files (*)")
        if not path:
            return
        try:
            with open(path, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
                self.editor.setPlainText(f.read())
            self.current_file = Path(path)
            self.status.showMessage(f"Opened: {self.current_file.name}", 5000)
            self.setWindowTitle(f"PestProfessor — {self.current_file.name}")
        except Exception as e:
            QMessageBox.critical(self, "Error", f"Could not open file:\n{e}")

    def save_file(self) -> None:
        if not self.current_file:
            return self.save_file_as()
        try:
            with open(self.current_file, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
                f.write(self.editor.toPlainText())
            self.status.showMessage(f"Saved: {self.current_file.name}", 5000)
        except Exception as e:
            QMessageBox.critical(self, "Error", f"Could not save file:\n{e}")

    def save_file_as(self) -> None:
        path, _ = QFileDialog.getSaveFileName(self, "Save File As", "", "Text Files (*.txt);;All Files (*)")
        if not path:
            return
        self.current_file = Path(path)
        self.save_file()
        self.setWindowTitle(f"PestProfessor — {self.current_file.name}")

    def about(self) -> None:
        QMessageBox.information(self, "About", "PestProfessor\nStarting layout using PyQt6")

    def closeEvent(self, event) -> None:
        if self.editor.document().isModified():
            resp = QMessageBox.question(
                self, "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Do you want to save before exiting?",
                QMessageBox.StandardButton.Save | QMessageBox.StandardButton.Discard | QMessageBox.StandardButton.Cancel
            )
            if resp == QMessageBox.StandardButton.Save:
                self.save_file()
                event.accept()
            elif resp == QMessageBox.StandardButton.Discard:
                event.accept()
            else:
                event.ignore()
        else:
            event.accept()


def main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:
    app = QApplication(argv or sys.argv)
    app.setApplicationName("PestProfessor")
    window = MainWindow()
    window.show()
    return app.exec()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    raise SystemExit(main())
